"n. 绑缚之物(尤指系住血管以免失血的线) 【记】 ligat(捆绑)+ure→捆 绑物→带子 【同】 同根词： ligament(韧带) n. 绷带 【根】ligat作为词根是""quot;连接""quot;的意思－用绷带来连接 【记】oblige 强制，义务，迫使，施恩惠；是绑着你让你做某事，强制；leg + 扯→扯腿的布→腿受伤扯的布 【相关】colligate 捆绑, 束, 综合，ligate (音:来给他(包扎伤口))结扎, 绑， obligate 使负义务 有责任的 ligature (n.)  c.1400, ""something used in tying or binding,"" from Middle French ligature (14c.), from Late Latin ligatura ""a band,"" from Latin ligatus, past participle of ligare ""to bind"" (see ligament). In musical notation from 1590s; of letters joined in printing or writing from 1690s."
